<2ND_LINE>PM-Politics-Quotes,240</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments Friday from the
presidential campaign trail:
   
   PRESIDENT REAGAN, at a spirited pre-convention sendoff for
George Bush: ``I suspect most people will vote for George Bush this
year because, after voting for him once or twice before, they know
he's their guarantee that peace and prosperity today will be
followed by peace and prosperity tomorrow. And frankly, I don't
think the American people want to gamble their future on a blind
date.''
   
   GEORGE BUSH, assailing Democrats while hailing Reagan: ``We all
know what will kill, definitively kill, this economic expansion
we've worked so hard to create. Those same Democrats, the McGovern
or Carter or Mondale Democrats, are just itching to get their hands
back on the levers that you operate so ably.''
   
   Illinois Gov. JAMES R. THOMPSON, said to be on the list of
Republican vice presidential possibilities, asking that his name be
withdrawn from consideration: ``The vice president's job requires a
lot of national and international travel. My wife couldn't travel
with me because I've got a 10-year-old in school, and that's not
true of the other candidates.''
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, saying he opposes new offshore drilling for oil
and gas, noting his efforts to block drilling off Massachusetts:
``I'm not a George-come-lately on this issue.''
</TEXT>
