<HEAD>U.S., Lao Officials To Meet on MIAs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U.S. and Laotian officials will meet later
this month to continue efforts at ascertaining the fate of American
servicemen missing in action from the Indochina war.
   The State Department said Friday that the meeting between
technical experts of both countries will take place Aug. 22-23 in
Vientiane, capital of Laos.
