<HEAD>Thunderstorms Continue Over Much Of The Nation</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Showers and thunderstorms remained today in southeast New York
state as well as the upper Mississippi Valley and northwest Texas,
from southern Arkansas to northern Louisiana, and across the upper
Plains into western Kansas.
   Thunderstorms in McCook, Neb., dropped more than 3 inches of
rain Friday and caused the Republican River to overflow its banks
and flood parts of the town. A downpour produced an inch of rain in
five minutes at Kulm, N.D.
   Among the heavier rainfalls during the six hours ending 2 a.m.
EDT today were more than 2 inches at North Platte, Neb., and almost
an inch at Grand Island, Neb. All other reports of rainfall during
the same period amounted to less than half an inch.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms in
Florida, Missouri, North Dakota and parts of Maine; from southeast
Louisiana across central Mississippi; across the upper Great Lakes;
and in the upper Mississippi Valley.
   High temperatures were expected to be in the 60s and 70s along
much of the California Coast and in the 70s over the northern
Pacific Coast; in the 70s and 80s in northern New England, the
upper Great Lakes, the northern Mississippi Valley, the Rockies and
other parts of the West; near 100 across southwest Texas; and 110
in the desert Southwest. The rest of the nation likely will hit the
90s.
   Temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 49 degrees at
Yellowstone, Wyo., to 93 at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 75 fair; Buffalo 76 foggy; Charleston, S.C. 75
fair; Cincinnati 72 foggy; Cleveland 76 partly cloudy; Detroit 75
foggy; Miami 80 fair; New York 79 hazy; Philadelphia 80 partly
cloudy; Pittsburgh 73 foggy; Portland, Maine 72 foggy; Washington
81 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 68 thunderstorms; Chicago 79 fair;
Dallas-Fort Worth 86 partly cloudy; Denver 62 fair; Des Moines 78
fair; Indianapolis 76 foggy; Kansas City 76 fair; Minneapolis-St.
Paul 79 partly cloudy; Nashville 77 fair; New Orleans 79 fair; St.
Louis 80 hazy.
   _West: Albuquerque 70 fair; Anchorage 53 partly cloudy; Las
Vegas 77 fair; Los Angeles 63 fair; Phoenix 93 fair; Salt Lake City
72 partly cloudy; San Diego 67 partly cloudy; San Francisco 59
cloudy; Seattle 58 fair.
   _Canada: Toronto 73 foggy.
