<HEAD>Doctor Charged With Murdering Wife, Daughter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALATINE, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 30-year-old physician was charged
Saturday with murdering his wife with a garden ax and drowning
their infant daughter.
   Dr. Lee E. Robin was charged with two counts of first-degree
murder and was being held without bond until a hearing Monday in
Cook County Circuit Court in Skokie, police said.
   The body of Annette Robin, 28, was found in an upstairs bedroom
and Denise, 2{ months, was discovered dead in a half-filled bathtub
