   The ax, three-feet long with a wooden handle, was found in the
bedroom near Mrs. Robin's body, Smith said.
   ``He (Robin) called police at 8:12 a.m. and indicated something
very bad had happened at his house,'' said Smith.
   Police Sgt. Dwain Nelson said he did not know whether a motive
had been determined.
   Robin had recently finished an internship at Humana Hospital in
Hoffman Estates, police said.
