<HEAD>Preliminary Soybean Price Support Set at $4.77 Bushel, Same as
Last Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soybean price support loan rates for the 1988
crop will be $4.77 per bushel, unchanged from last year, although a
final decision will be made by Oct. 1, Agriculture Secretary
Richard E. Lyng announced Friday.
   The loan rate for 1988 soybeans is far below current market
prices of more than $8 per bushel. Prices rose sharply this summer
as drought and hot weather reduced harvest prospects.
   On Thursday, USDA estimated this fall's soybean harvest at 1.47
billion bushels, down 23 percent from 1987.
