($525,000) in the safe,'' Rover said Thursday. ``Then he tied me
up. It's a good thing the painter came or I would have been a dead
duck.''
   He said the robber also took $7,000 in jewelry and some cash.
   Detectives said Rover may be able to recoup on the stocks and
Treasury bills.
   Asked why he did not keep his valuables in the bank, Rover said,
``I have other money in the bank.''
