<FILEID>AP-NR-08-13-88 0800EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>d f PM-OilPrices     08-13 0223</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Oil Prices,0236</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Oil Futures Head Lower</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: For Saturday PMs</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Oil futures prices headed lower again on what
analysts described as technical factors.
   On the New York Mercantile Exchange, the contract for September
delivery of West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark grade of U.S.
crude oil, closed down 24 cents Friday to $15.52 a 42-gallon
barrel. The contract had risen 5 cents on Thursday.
   Refined petroleum products also headed lower Friday. Unleaded
gasoline for September delivery fell 0.52 cent to close at 46.02
cents a gallon, after rising 0.45 cent Thursday.
   Heating oil, which rose 0.41 cent in the previous session, fell
0.56 cent to finish at 44 cents a gallon.
   ``I think a lot of today's activity was technical,'' said Peter
Beutel, an oil analyst with Elders Futures Inc. ``There's no news
that I'm aware of.''
   Beutel said the market remained in a holding pattern, awaiting
word on what action OPEC might take to help prop up sagging
worldwide prices.
   Oil prices have declined in recent months amid reports that some
members of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries had
exceeded their official production quotas.
   Prices rebounded in recent days after news of a United
Nations-sponsored effort to end the fighting between Iran and Iraq,
two members of OPEC.
   Analysts attributed Thursday's rise primarily to speculative
buying.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
